<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-10496] Wrong IntRange.by(...) behaviour for left-open ranges</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-10496</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Call &lt;tt&gt;by&lt;/tt&gt; on &lt;tt&gt;IntRange&lt;/tt&gt; results in loss of information about inclusion of the left border, because &lt;tt&gt;inclusiveLeft&lt;/tt&gt; flag is not passed into &lt;tt&gt;NumberRange&lt;/tt&gt; constructor.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For example, &lt;tt&gt;5 in (5&amp;lt;..20)&lt;/tt&gt; gives &lt;tt&gt;false&lt;/tt&gt; when &lt;tt&gt;5 in (5&amp;lt;..20).by(2)&lt;/tt&gt; gives &lt;tt&gt;true&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While with &lt;tt&gt;NumberRange&lt;/tt&gt; &lt;tt&gt;5 in (5L&amp;lt;..20)&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;5 in (5L&amp;lt;..20).by(2)&lt;/tt&gt; both gives &lt;tt&gt;false&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also with &lt;tt&gt;@CompileStatic&lt;/tt&gt; even &lt;tt&gt;5 in (5&amp;lt;..20)&lt;/tt&gt; gives &lt;tt&gt;true&lt;/tt&gt;, because new parameter lost in &lt;tt&gt;RangeExpressionTransformer&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
